body_html:
@moveforever The key in your error message is this part:

  '/lib/gcc/x86_64-redhat-linux/4.8.3/include/limits.h'
  '/lib/gcc/x86_64-redhat-linux/4.8.3/include/syslimits.h'
  '/lib/gcc/x86_64-redhat-linux/4.8.3/include/stddef.h'
  '/lib/gcc/x86_64-redhat-linux/4.8.3/include/stdarg.h'
  '/lib/gcc/x86_64-redhat-linux/4.8.3/include/stdint.h'.

You may need to reinstall gcc and g++.

@amel2houwi please file a new issue by filling out the full form. If you are on windows, this is a known issue. If you check out r1.0 branch, you should be able to build fine.

@moveforever The key in your error message is this part:
```
  '/lib/gcc/x86_64-redhat-linux/4.8.3/include/limits.h'
  '/lib/gcc/x86_64-redhat-linux/4.8.3/include/syslimits.h'
  '/lib/gcc/x86_64-redhat-linux/4.8.3/include/stddef.h'
  '/lib/gcc/x86_64-redhat-linux/4.8.3/include/stdarg.h'
  '/lib/gcc/x86_64-redhat-linux/4.8.3/include/stdint.h'.
```
You may need to reinstall gcc and g++.
